MOTION TO COMPEL OR CONTINUE
COMES now the Plaintiff/Father, Christopher Blaine McGregor, by and through his attorney
of record, Dianne James Davis, and states the following facts:
1. On October 16, 2025, Defendant filed a “SUMMATION OF SERVICES RENDERED
PER THIS CASE” Report from Kelly Turner, Counselor at The Bridges, in AlaCourt at
8:36 p.m. which was the evening before the final hearing on October 17, 2025.
2. Plaintiff filed a Motion to Strike said filing and this Court denied said motion;
3. The Final Hearing on October 17, 2025, was continued until October 30, 2025, at the
request of Defendant’s Counsel;
4. Plaintiff immediately subpoenaed Kelly Turner to appear in Court on October 30, 2025,
and said subpoena was served on Monday, October 20, 2025;
5. Kelly Turner emailed Plaintiff’s Counsel’s Office on October 20, 2025, stating she will
not be available as she will be out of town – a copy of this email is attached at Exhibit
“A”;
6. That said “Summation” written by Kelly Turner and filed by Defendant is full of hearsay
and Plaintiff’s Counsel has the right to cross-examine Kelly Turner.
7. Furthermore, the Defendant’s current husband, Bradley Cleckler, was subpoenaed to
appear in Court on October 17, 2025; however, after the continuance, Mr. Cleckler
contacted Counsel’s Office and stated he cannot get off work on October 30, 2025,
because the other two (2) employees in his department are taking off. Mr. Cleckler is a
vital witness in this case and his attendance is necessary.
DOCUMENT 389
WHEREFORE, the premises considered, Plaintiff requests this Court to either enter an
Order compelling Kelly Turner and Bradley Cleckler to appear in Court on October 30, 2025, at
9:00 am or continue the final hearing in this matter until such time as Kelly Turner and Bradley
Cleckler are available.
Respectfully submitted this the 21st day of October, 2025.
